<author><name><![CDATA[lidnariq]]></name></author>
<updated>2015-02-25T18:29:41-07:00</updated>
<published>2015-02-25T18:29:41-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12431&amp;p=142085#p142085</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12431&amp;p=142085#p142085"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Duplicating data on SNES games for bigger memories]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12431&amp;p=142085#p142085"><![CDATA[
ALL SNES games are made from one or two ROMs where both are powers of two in size.<br /><br />Clock Tower is 3 MiB = 2 MiB + 1 MiB, and it is mirrored by duplicating the last 1 MiB.<br /><br />Now that you have a explicitly mirrored form that is a power of two in size, you just duplicate that chunk as needed.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3512">lidnariq</a> — Wed Feb 25, 2015 6:29 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
